messages.content:
Now I understand the task. I need to create a CSS Grid layout with:
- Header spanning full width at top
- Sidebar on the left (250px fixed width)
- Main content on the right (takes remaining space)
- Footer spanning full width at bottom
- Minimum page height should be 100vh
- Use semantic grid-area names

I need to create a file called `layout.css` in the current directory.

Let me create this CSS file with proper grid layout.</think>```bash
cat <<'EOF' > layout.css
/* Task 2.2: CSS Grid Layout */

.page-container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-areas:
    "header header"
    "sidebar main"
    "footer footer";
  grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr;
  grid-template-rows: auto 1fr auto;
  min-height: 100vh;
  gap: 20px;
  padding: 20px;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

/* Semantic grid-area names */
.header {
  grid-area: header;
  background-color: #f0f0f0;
  padding: 20px;
  text-align: center;
}

.sidebar {
  grid-area: sidebar;
  background-color: #e0e0e0;
  padding: 20px;
}

.main {
  grid-area: main;
  background-color: #d0d0d0;
  padding: 20px;
}

.footer {
  grid-area: footer;
  background-color: #f0f0f0;
  padding: 20px;
  text-align: center;
}
EOF
```

